{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":109965,"duration_api_ms":109190,"num_turns":20,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"6eb0fa95-86e0-4ee3-89f3-f00e6b2de968","total_cost_usd":0.9512985,"usage":{"input_tokens":18,"cache_creation_input_tokens":58060,"cache_read_input_tokens":974817,"output_tokens":4037,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":58060,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":18,"outputTokens":4037,"cacheReadInputTokens":974817,"cacheCreationInputTokens":58060,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.9512985,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 68 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored)","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly (no warnings)","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","model.rs: TaskRunEntry has all required fields — milestone_id (line 275), bead_id (278), project_id (280), run_id (282), plan_hash (285), outcome (288), outcome_detail (290), started_at (293), finished_at (296) — all new optional fields use serde(default, skip_serializing_if) for backward compatibility","model.rs: MilestoneProgress.skipped_beads (line 203) with serde(default), remaining() accounts for it (line 213)","model.rs: MilestoneEventType::BeadSkipped variant (line 240) and TaskRunOutcome::Skipped (line 306) with is_terminal() returning true","model.rs: validate_semantics (line 172) rejects Active without active_bead and terminal with active_bead","service.rs: TaskRunLineagePort::update_task_run (line 82) now returns AppResult<TaskRunEntry> — the canonical finalized entry for downstream use","service.rs: record_bead_completion (line 484) delegates entirely to update_task_run — single completion path, no second append","service.rs: update_task_run (line 550) validates terminal outcome (line 564), calls lineage update (line 572), then reconciles snapshot from canonical lineage via reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage (line 585-589), validates snapshot semantics (line 592), writes snapshot (line 593), and deduplicates journal events before appending (lines 599-609)","service.rs: reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage (line 194) rebuilds in_progress/completed/failed/skipped counters from lineage, recomputes active_bead from non-terminal entries, and transitions status from Active to Ready when no active beads remain (line 246-248) — this fixes the prior invariant violation where Active persisted with no active_bead","service.rs: record_bead_start (line 422) calls validate_snapshot (line 465) before write_snapshot (line 466)","service.rs: normalize_task_runs (line 157) collapses legacy paired start/completion rows for accurate counter reconciliation","fs.rs: update_task_run (line ~2584-2632) handles idempotent replay — when entry is already terminal with matching outcome, it backfills missing optional metadata (run_id, plan_hash, outcome_detail) without rejecting; only rejects when the replay has conflicting values (option_conflicts at line 2334)","fs.rs: backfill_terminal_entry (line 2338) only writes to disk when metadata was actually backfilled (returns bool), avoiding unnecessary I/O on pure replays","Test: completion_retry_repairs_snapshot_and_journal_without_double_counting (line 1640) verifies: (a) first completion fails at journal write but lineage and snapshot are updated, (b) snapshot after failure passes validate_semantics with status=Ready (not Active), (c) replayed completion succeeds via idempotent lineage accept, (d) final snapshot has correct counters, (e) journal has exactly 1 completion event (no duplicates)","Test: bead_start_and_completion_tracking (line ~1420+) verifies end-to-end flow with runs.len()==1","Test: multiple_retries_visible_for_same_bead verifies start→fail→start→succeed cycle with both attempts visible in find_runs_for_bead","Test: completion_flow_rejects_duplicate_finalization verifies conflicting terminal updates are rejected","Test: lineage_updates_require_run_id_when_multiple_open_attempts_exist verifies ambiguity rejection and exact run_id matching","Test: task_run_entry_backward_compat_without_new_fields verifies old JSON without new fields deserializes correctly","Test: find_runs_for_bead_collapses_legacy_start_completion_pairs verifies legacy paired-row handling","Test: skipped_runs_are_tracked_without_counting_as_failures verifies skipped_beads counter and BeadSkipped journal event"],"findings_or_gaps":["The two defects identified in prior final-review amendments (fr-3-b8dbc656 and fr-3-9fecdf73) have both been addressed in this round: (1) Idempotency: update_task_run in the FS adapter now accepts replays of the same terminal payload with matching outcome, and the service layer reconciles snapshot state from canonical lineage rather than incrementing counters, so a retry after partial failure correctly repairs drift. (2) Invariant preservation: reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage transitions status from Active to Ready when no active beads remain (line 246-248), and validate_snapshot is called before write_snapshot (line 592), ensuring Active-without-active_bead is never persisted.","The outstanding_risk noted by the implementor — that completion still spans lineage, snapshot, and journal writes without a cross-file transaction — is now mitigated rather than eliminated. A crash after lineage write but before snapshot/journal write leaves the system in a state that can be repaired by replaying the same completion call. This is an acceptable trade-off for file-based storage.","AppError::RunStartFailed is still used (service.rs line 565) for rejecting non-terminal outcomes in update_task_run. A more specific error variant would be semantically cleaner but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue.","Journal deduplication (lines 599-605) compares all four fields (timestamp, event_type, bead_id, details) for exact match. This is correct for the replay scenario but could theoretically miss an event if any detail field changes between attempts (e.g., different finished_at timestamp). However, since the finalized_run's finished_at is used consistently, this should not occur in practice.","The FailSecondJournalAppend test mock (lines 624-651) only fails the second append_event call (the completion event after the bead-start event), which correctly simulates a journal failure during completion while allowing the bead-start journal event to succeed. This is a well-designed regression test."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"913f6a13-c1e1-4bde-be5f-402723d99757"}
